## Executive Summary

The TapAuth Android server implementation has achieved **100% specification compliance**. All critical (P0) and high-priority (P1) requirements from the protocol specification have been successfully implemented and tested.

---

## ✅ Compliance Checklist

### Critical Requirements (P0) - 100% Complete

- [x] **UDP Port 36692** - Specification-compliant port
  - Changed from 8442 to 36692
  - Updated in AuthenticationService.kt and HomeScreen.kt
  
- [x] **Replay Attack Mitigation** - Security requirement
  - Nonce cache with 120-second expiry
  - 60-second timestamp validation window
  - Integrated into UDP and BLE services

### High Priority Requirements (P1) - 100% Complete

- [x] **Server Retransmission Strategy** - Reliability requirement
  - Fixed 500ms interval per specification
  - Supports UDP and BLE transports
  - Automatic cleanup on timeout or confirmation

- [x] **GrantConfirmation Message Support** - Protocol requirement
  - JNI parsing functions implemented
  - Data classes and protobuf support
  - Ready for client integration

- [x] **Proper EncryptedPacket Serialization** - Protocol requirement
  - WrapperMessage with AuthenticationGrant payload
  - Correct protobuf structure per specification
  - Temporal identifier generation
  - CSK-based encryption with proper nonce derivation

- [x] **AuthenticationCancel Support** - Protocol requirement
  - JNI parsing functions implemented
  - Ready for multi-device scenarios

